HEADWORD: Reducing agent
<hw>Re*du"cing a`gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>a substance that causes reduction of another
substance in a chemical reaction, as by donating electrons or adding
hydrogen atoms; <as>as, lithium hydride is a powerful <ex>reducing
agent</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

